          p Open-source alternatives: Moses, Marian, OpenNMT
          p Some special-purpose systems: Apertium, Joshua
        section
          h2 Computer-Aided Translation
          ul
            li Translation Memory
            li Translation suggestions
            li Quality estimation
            li Post-editing
        section
          h2 Bilingual Communication
          ul
            li Translation
            li Interpreting
            li Multilingual communication
          p Still very challenging
        section(data-background-image="img/translation_error_2.jpeg")
        section(data-background-image="img/translation_error_3.jpg")
        section(data-background-image="img/translation_error_1.webp")
        section(data-background-image="img/translation_error_4.jpg")
        section
          h2 Why is MT so hard?
          ul
            li Translation depends on context
            ul
              li "Black Eye" is "<span style="color:blue;">blaues</span> Auge" (<em>blue eye</em>) in German and "ojo <span style="color:violet">morado</span>" (<em>violet eye </em>) in Spanish
            li Subtle difference matter
            ul
              li "value" can mean "worth", "price" or "importance" in different contexts
        section
          h2 Reordering
          img(src="img/jap_reordering1.svg")
        section
          h2 Reordering
          img(src="img/jap_reordering2.svg")
        section
          h2 Long-distance dependencies
          ul
            li English: I saw the <span style="color:hotpink">movie</span> and <span style="color:mediumblue">it<span> was great!
            li(class="fragment") German: Ich sah <span style="color:hotpink">den Film</span> und <span style="color:mediumblue">er (he)</span> was prima!
            li(class="fragment") Spanish: Vi <span style="color:hotpink">la película</span> y <span style="color:mediumblue">ella (she)</span> fue súper!
        section
          h2 Semantic issues
          ul
            li John liked Michael, so he<sub style="font-size:0.5em">JOHN</sub> helped him<sub style="font-size:0.5em">MICHAEL</sub>
            li John liked Michael, as he<sub style="font-size:0.5em">MICHAEL</sub> helped him<sub style="font-size:0.5em">JOHN</sub>
        section
          h2 Missing Information in Translation
          ul
            li English: "Cousin"
            li German: "Vetter" (male) / "Cousine" (female)
            li Chinese:
            table(style="font-size:0.5em")
